From: Shigeru Yoshida <syoshida@redhat.com>
Date: Tue, 16 Jul 2024 11:09:05 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] tipc: Return non-zero value from tipc_udp_addr2str() on error
Git-commit: fa96c6baef1b5385e2f0c0677b32b3839e716076
Patch-mainline: v6.11-rc1
References: CVE-2024-42284 bsc#1229382

tipc_udp_addr2str() should return non-zero value if the UDP media
address is invalid. Otherwise, a buffer overflow access can occur in
tipc_media_addr_printf(). Fix this by returning 1 on an invalid UDP
media address.

Fixes: d0f91938bede ("tipc: add ip/udp media type")
Signed-off-by: Shigeru Yoshida <syoshida@redhat.com>
Reviewed-by: Tung Nguyen <tung.q.nguyen@endava.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.com>
---
 net/tipc/udp_media.c |    5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/net/tipc/udp_media.c
+++ b/net/tipc/udp_media.c
@@ -135,8 +135,11 @@ static int tipc_udp_addr2str(struct tipc
 		snprintf(buf, size, "%pI4:%u", &ua->ipv4, ntohs(ua->port));
 	else if (ntohs(ua->proto) == ETH_P_IPV6)
 		snprintf(buf, size, "%pI6:%u", &ua->ipv6, ntohs(ua->port));
-	else
+	else {
 		pr_err("Invalid UDP media address\n");
+		return 1;
+	}
+
 	return 0;
 }
 
